text: The economy rice here is a little saltier than that at the economy rice stall at the neighboring kopitiam, Food Loft but is decent for the prices they charge. Price wise, both stalls sell the same 1 meat-1 vege-1 egg combo at $3.3. The tehsi-siudai ($1.6 for takeaway) here is alright. Paynow/paylah are available.

This review is dedicated to the fish soup stall. Best fish soup hands down, not too expensive, fish is fresh and thick. Aunties running the shop are so friendly and they remember their customers really well ðŸ¥° they are so heart warming and endearing, highly recommended!!!!

Racist brown colour hair auntie at the beverage store.

I ordered 1 cold barley and 1 teh peng to drink at the store and I ordered in Chinese, auntie keep replying me with English instead and give takeaway cup. I asked for glass since Iâ€™m having it here and auntie reply that she knows Iâ€™m having it here.
I asked why she didnâ€™t give me glass and she said since she pour to plastic cup alr might as well I need to pay.

So she marked up the price for me.

This is not the first time I came to this place and ordered from the stall yet she dare to do this to foreigners.
Friendly service from Kimly Dim Sum stall. Good variety too.
Besides the grilled sotong from another stall, I ordered the wanton noodles,  and a plate of char siew. Sumptuous. Try this stall.  CDC vouchers accepted. Worth a try!
